COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 524, L.D. 1294
1 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
2 number to read consecutively.
3 SUMMARY
44 This amendment replaces the bill. The amendment doubles the dependent exemption
55 tax credit for a child or dependent who has not attained 6 years of age by the end of the tax
66 year and phases out the refundability of the tax credit based on income.
77 The amendment also adds an appropriations and allocations section.
